fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let (S \triangleright  P, \iota ^S, \otimes ^S, \text {pr}^S) and (T \triangleright  Q, \iota ^T, \otimes ^T, \text {pr}^T) be lmf-containers. We define their direct composite as the lmf-container (S \triangleright  P \circ  T \triangleright  Q, \iota , \otimes , \text {pr}) where

       \begin {align*}            \iota  &:= (\iota ^S , \lambda  \_ . \iota ^T)\\     (s , f) \otimes  (s' , f') &:= (s \otimes ^S s' , \lambda  p . f\ (\text {pr}^S_1\ p) \otimes ^T f'\ (\text {pr}^S_2\ p))\\     \text {pr}\ (p , q) &:= ((\text {pr}^S_1\ p , \text {pr}^T_1\ q) , (\text {pr}^S_2\ p , \text {pr}^T_2\ q))        \end {align*}   

  This is a generalisation of the direct product of monoids.
